Two coffees coming up.

04:58.715 --> 05:00.759
Old cedar and fresh flowers.

05:01.343 --> 05:02.928
Never get tired of
the smell in here.

05:04.387 --> 05:06.431
Afternoon, Bart. What you got?

05:06.932 --> 05:08.117
I got elk steaks.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.202
I got squab.

05:09.226 --> 05:11.436
I got... wild boar.

05:12.604 --> 05:15.440
- Is there anything you can't catch?
- Yeah, a break.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.376
You interested?

05:17.400 --> 05:19.253
You know, Connie loves
these elk steaks.

05:19.277 --> 05:21.255
She'd kill me if I didn't
bring something home.

05:21.279 --> 05:22.739
I was kind of counting on that.

05:23.198 --> 05:24.133
Hi, Parker.

05:24.157 --> 05:25.408
Hello, Bart.

05:27.536 --> 05:28.620
Here you go.

05:29.788 --> 05:32.707
You still making that stuff?
Moonshine will drive you crazy.

05:33.416 --> 05:34.793
The way I look at it,

05:35.418 --> 05:38.981
we live on this tiny little rock that's
flying through the blackness of space

05:39.005 --> 05:40.900
at about, what,
60,000 miles an hour?

05:40.924 --> 05:43.069
And there's only one
damn way to get off it.

05:43.093 --> 05:45.854
If that thought don't make you crazy,
I don't know what the hell will.

05:47.681 --> 05:50.493
I guess you're right. Never
thought of it that way.

05:50.517 --> 05:53.621
That's because you spend most of your
time stuck standing behind this counter.

05:53.645 --> 05:56.958
You need to get out, Maynard,
and breathe some life.

05:56.982 --> 05:59.126
I suppose I do. I suppose I do.

05:59.150 --> 06:01.003
It all goes by in a flash, pal.

06:01.027 --> 06:04.698
I mean, trust me, one day you'll wake up
and go, "Where the hell did it all go?"

06:06.908 --> 06:08.869
For the next time you
wanna get a little crazy.

06:11.079 --> 06:12.205
All right. Thanks.

06:12.664 --> 06:14.916
- So, just the elk steaks?
- That'll do it.

06:15.417 --> 06:18.312
Tell that pretty little wife of
yours she has excellent taste.

06:18.336 --> 06:19.438
Will do.

06:19.462 --> 06:21.715
Old cedar and fresh
flowers, I love it.

06:22.716 --> 06:23.717
Love it!

06:32.767 --> 06:35.061
Hey, Park, you mind
doing me a favor?

06:35.437 --> 06:36.605
Of course. What's up?

06:37.022 --> 06:39.357
You mind closing up tonight,
running to the bank?

06:40.191 --> 06:41.860
What happened, your
house on fire?

06:42.235 --> 06:45.488
I just wanna surprise
Connie, you know?

06:46.781 --> 06:48.325
Go home, grill up these steaks.

06:49.034 --> 06:50.452
A nice bottle of wine.

06:50.911 --> 06:51.912
Some flowers.

06:53.330 --> 06:54.623
Breathe a little life.

06:55.206 --> 06:56.291
Sweet, Maynard.

06:57.042 --> 06:58.043
Yeah, I'll close up.

06:58.627 --> 06:59.628
All right.

07:01.004 --> 07:02.047
Great.

