- Start doing movies like we talked about.
- That's what I'm saying.

41:35.118 --> 41:36.369
So what do you think?

41:38.496 --> 41:39.497
Crikey!

41:42.709 --> 41:44.979
I know. This face is such
a movie face, right?

41:45.003 --> 41:46.212
Such good face.

41:47.588 --> 41:48.588
Yeah?

41:49.048 --> 41:50.048
Bart, it's me.

41:50.383 --> 41:51.676
Who the hell is me?

41:52.135 --> 41:53.386
It's me, Bart. It's Jack.

41:56.014 --> 41:57.140
The sheriff.

41:57.890 --> 42:00.226
If you've come for my
still, you can piss off.

42:00.601 --> 42:02.437
I'm not here for
the still, Bart.

42:02.645 --> 42:05.148
Look, I got a couple of people
out here who wanna talk to you.

42:06.149 --> 42:07.692
People from the TV studio.

42:11.904 --> 42:12.904
Hi.

42:13.656 --> 42:17.160
- What do you want?
- We want you to help us catch Bigfoot.

42:18.536 --> 42:19.513
How much?

42:19.537 --> 42:21.956
We can pay you 5,000 dollars.

42:22.248 --> 42:26.669
Five thousand to go with you,
10,000 to find him and catch him.

42:31.924 --> 42:33.718
- Fine.
- And we do it my way.

42:34.052 --> 42:35.887
- Meaning what?
- We go alone.

42:36.054 --> 42:38.139
You and me alone in the woods?

42:39.057 --> 42:41.493
What about the crew? We
have a whole show to shoot.

42:41.517 --> 42:42.894
I suggest you bring your camera.

42:43.311 --> 42:44.329
Not quite that simple, mate.

42:44.353 --> 42:46.331
- We can figure it out.
- There's hair and makeup and such.

42:46.355 --> 42:49.001
We're not going to catch imps and fairies.
We're going out to catch...

42:49.025 --> 42:50.586
You know what? I'm coming with.

42:50.610 --> 42:52.050
- The hell you are.
- Actually, wait.

42:52.111 --> 42:54.238
I think... that, actually,
is a very good idea.

42:54.363 --> 42:56.282
Bart, I'm the sheriff, okay?

42:56.407 --> 42:58.487
And if we're gonna catch
Bigfoot, I'm gonna be there.

42:58.534 --> 42:59.744
It's a great idea.

42:59.952 --> 43:02.413
Alright, the three of us.

43:04.040 --> 43:07.210
We ain't opening a beauty parlor.
By the truck in ten.

43:08.211 --> 43:09.146
Go on.

43:09.170 --> 43:10.171
Ten minutes by the truck.

43:10.546 --> 43:11.672
We love your house.

43:14.425 --> 43:17.071
Couldn't be a beauty parlor
under the circumstances.

43:17.095 --> 43:19.097
I just don't understand
even the reference.

43:23.184 --> 43:24.578
Keep the change. Don't
worry about it.

43:24.602 --> 43:26.914
Gee, thanks. Enjoy your
stay in Pottersville.

43:26.938 --> 43:28.022
Let's go, boys.

43:37.824 --> 43:40.886
I suppose the next thing
you're gonna tell me

43:40.910 --> 43:42.763
is that you had
lunch with Bigfoot.

43:42.787 --> 43:44.723
Did he ask for his pants back?

43:44.747 --> 43:45.933
Are you calling me fat?

43:45.957 --> 43:49.812
- If the shoe fits...
- Ladies, what in the world?

43:49.836 --> 43:52.648
She's trying to say that she's
seen Bigfoot more than I have.

43:52.672 --> 43:56.342
But everybody knows she's just
trying to get on the show.

43:56.467 --> 43:57.718
All right, that's enough.

43:58.386 --> 44:00.638
You two should be
ashamed of yourselves.

44:03.766 --> 44:06.727
Good Lord, what is
going on around here?

44:08.771 --> 44:09.939
Thank you.

44:10.648 --> 44:14.753
Step right up, folks, get your
brand new Bigfoot merchandise.

44:14.777 --> 44:18.257
That's right. Get it while
we still have a Bigfoot.

44:18.281 --> 44:20.281
What did you mean, "while
we still have a Bigfoot"?

44:20.575 --> 44:21.927
Because of Bart.

44:21.951 --> 44:24.263
- What about him?
- You didn't hear?

44:24.287 --> 44:26.038
They're putting him
on Monster Finder.

44:26.706 --> 44:27.706
What?

44:28.416 --> 44:31.103
You know Bart, if anybody can
catch Bigfoot, it's him.

44:31.127 --> 44:32.587
- Let's get these unpacked.
- Okay.

44:33.504 --> 44:34.547
You got it.

44:39.343 --> 44:40.428
Guns, huh?

44:42.471 --> 44:45.808
How the hell did you think we were gonna
catch him, with a big butterfly net?

44:46.642 --> 44:49.020
Oh, yeah. We can't
kill it, right?

44:49.520 --> 44:50.980
Just tranq' guns, Brock.

44:51.314 --> 44:52.607
Make him go beddie-byes.

44:53.357 --> 44:54.734
Right, tranq' guns.

44:55.359 --> 44:57.754
- Tranq' guns, Eileen, I knew that.
- What?

44:57.778 --> 44:59.882
I was testing you guys. Of
course they are tranq' guns.

44:59.906 --> 45:02.909
Sheriff, would you be a doll?
I got a bit of a Yoga injury.

45:04.702 --> 45:06.996
I got a Yoga injury. Thank you.

45:08.456 --> 45:09.457
Thanks, lovely.

45:11.792 --> 45:15.480
I wish they'd find whoever's doing
it and just be done with it already.

45:15.504 --> 45:16.547
Doing what?

45:16.672 --> 45:17.965
Pretending to be Bigfoot.

45:19.467 --> 45:21.552
How do you know it's
someone pretending?

45:23.095 --> 45:25.264
Because there's no such
thing as a Bigfoot.

45:26.057 --> 45:27.058
Hmm.

45:30.770 --> 45:32.456
What's all that crap?

45:32.480 --> 45:34.357
Just a few essentials.
Some night vision.

45:34.815 --> 45:36.359
Helmet cam, light meter.

45:36.692 --> 45:39.004
Pheromone spectrometer
which is my own design.

45:39.028 --> 45:42.198
It reads the pheromones
of beasts or monsters.

45:42.490 --> 45:44.116
You're so great, why
do you need me?

45:45.326 --> 45:47.703
- Jack, pick up that tent, would you?
- Tent?

45:49.163 --> 45:50.748
Are we spending the night?

45:51.040 --> 45:53.060
What did you think, we were
going for a couple hours,

45:53.084 --> 45:55.795
be back in time for you to
watch Dancing with the Stars?

45:56.170 --> 45:58.381
This is a hunt, not
a day at the spa.

45:58.798 --> 46:01.193
How long are we
planning on staying?

46:01.217 --> 46:02.593
Until we catch him!

46:03.052 --> 46:07.848
Okay, Mr. Singing Dancing Television
Man, times-a-wasting. Get in the car.

46:09.100 --> 46:10.643
What? You'll be fine.

46:11.602 --> 46:13.562
- You'll be fine.
- Oh, my God.

46:13.896 --> 46:16.107
I'll try and bring him
back in one piece.

46:20.111 --> 46:21.279
Give me a break.

46:21.696 --> 46:24.240
I bet a dollar to a dime that

46:24.699 --> 46:27.994
it's just some prankster out there
having a big laugh at our expense.

46:28.536 --> 46:30.830
But if it's a hoax, I don't
think he's trying to be mean.

46:31.205 --> 46:32.915
Look at how happy
he's made everybody.

46:33.666 --> 46:35.751
At first, but the whole
town has changed.

46:35.918 --> 46:38.713
Now everyone is dying to get
on that stupid TV show.

46:38.921 --> 46:42.508
I think they're just looking for
something that gives them a little hope.

46:46.470 --> 46:51.851
So, if it's not really a Bigfoot,
if it's just some guy pretending,

46:51.976 --> 46:54.096
what do you think they'll do
to him if they catch him?

46:55.479 --> 46:58.482
Hell, knowing Bart, probably shoot
him and hang his head on the wall.

47:04.864 --> 47:06.032
I'll get him.

47:10.077 --> 47:11.787
I'm just outside
of Pottersville,

47:12.038 --> 47:14.957
where it is nine o'clock
in the post meridian.

47:15.374 --> 47:19.503
And, ladies and gentlemen, for the
first time in Monster Finder history,

47:20.087 --> 47:25.718
this find has proven to be so treacherous
that I am out here completely alone.

47:26.135 --> 47:30.782
Aided only by the sheriff,
for legal reasons,

47:30.806 --> 47:32.767
and a local guide...

47:34.101 --> 47:35.412
who is quite curmudgeonly.

47:35.436 --> 47:36.854
What the hell is he doing?

47:39.065 --> 47:40.649
I think he's filming
his TV show.

47:41.108 --> 47:42.860
Is that thing gonna
be on the whole time?

47:43.027 --> 47:46.781
Guys, please. I'm filming my show. That
means I've gotta capture everything.

47:47.448 --> 47:48.574
Sorry.

47:49.950 --> 47:50.951
Can we watch?

47:51.077 --> 47:54.330
Yes. In fact, I think you should
watch, so you can get ready.

47:54.538 --> 47:55.706
For what?

47:56.207 --> 47:59.418
For the Bigfoot, mate.
For the Bigfoot.

48:00.336 --> 48:06.550
Now, I shall try to
communicate with the beast.

48:12.723 --> 48:14.475
You having bowel problems?

48:15.184 --> 48:16.936
I'm communicating
with the Squatch.

48:17.478 --> 48:18.562
By yodeling?

48:19.188 --> 48:22.483
- It's a mating call.
- Oh. So you wanna hump Bigfoot?

48:24.819 --> 48:25.945
It's a coyote.

48:26.278 --> 48:28.072
That's his way of
communicating with us.

48:28.280 --> 48:29.508
It's a coyote.

48:29.532 --> 48:30.699
Very specifically...

48:31.200 --> 48:36.038
there's a Squatch
pretending to be a coyote.

48:36.664 --> 48:37.664
It just gets wilder.

48:38.082 --> 48:39.333
That's what the Squatch does.

48:41.085 --> 48:42.085
See.

48:42.545 --> 48:44.046
Definitely a coyote.

48:44.213 --> 48:45.214
Okay, fine.

48:46.173 --> 48:48.568
- That's for sure. It's a coyote.
- Definitely a coyote.

48:48.592 --> 48:50.845
Fine...

48:51.971 --> 48:53.264
Get out a secret weapon.

48:54.098 --> 48:55.182
Secret weapon.

48:56.392 --> 48:59.061
You gonna write another one
of them Yeti love songs?

49:01.230 --> 49:04.859
A secret weapon against the Squatch...
is our humanity.

49:05.860 --> 49:09.989
So we shall try to lure him
in with the gift of melody.

49:10.781 --> 49:13.885
Maybe we're gonna have one of them...
Bigfoot hoe-downs.

49:13.909 --> 49:15.453
I hope you got some
more moonshine.

49:30.426 --> 49:32.404
- What?
- You're gonna wake the whole county.

49:32.428 --> 49:35.323
- You think it's stupid, don't you?
- No, I don't think you're stupid.

49:35.347 --> 49:38.893
I just think maybe sometimes when it
comes to thinking, you have bad luck.

49:39.185 --> 49:41.985
I don't understand why it's not working.
It worked perfectly last time.

49:53.032 --> 49:56.136
I hear you, brother, but I've laid bait
and tripwire around the perimeter,

49:56.160 --> 49:57.745
so we'll know when he's coming.

50:01.499 --> 50:03.101
Bait and tripwire. Is that safe?

50:12.134 --> 50:13.134
You okay?

50:14.178 --> 50:15.387
Do you want me to do that?

50:15.888 --> 50:17.056
No, I'm fine.

50:17.932 --> 50:19.600
You can take off if you want.

50:19.975 --> 50:21.352
I'll wait till you're done.

50:22.019 --> 50:24.438
I'll get the bank bag, I can
drop it off on my way home.

50:25.940 --> 50:27.107
Great. Thanks.

51:07.398 --> 51:08.398
Thanks.

51:13.529 --> 51:14.529
What?

51:15.614 --> 51:16.907
Do you need anything else?

51:18.367 --> 51:20.244
Nope, all good.

51:21.161 --> 51:22.204
Thanks for doing it.

51:24.456 --> 51:25.708
Good night, Maynard.

51:52.401 --> 51:53.652
What the hell was that?

51:55.529 --> 51:58.949
- What am I supposed to do with this?
- If you see Bigfoot, shoot him.

52:03.704 --> 52:07.475
I've set up bait and tripwire
around the perimeter of the camp,

52:07.499 --> 52:10.586
and the tripwire has
just been tripped.

52:10.753 --> 52:14.423
So, let's see if we've
got ourselves a Squatch.

52:17.176 --> 52:18.176
What the...?

52:18.969 --> 52:21.597
I think I got him. I
think I got Bigfoot!

52:25.559 --> 52:26.559
What happened?

52:26.977 --> 52:28.354
You shot Jack.

52:32.691 --> 52:35.045
- Where's Bigfoot?
- There's no Bigfoot.

52:35.069 --> 52:39.406
It was just one of your coyotes looking for
a romantic evening of dinner and song.

52:40.032 --> 52:43.494
- Is he gonna be all right?
- He'll be all right, just taking a nap.

52:44.161 --> 52:45.454
Nobody died on this trip.

52:46.955 --> 52:47.956
Yet.

52:55.714 --> 52:57.966
'Cause I'll find
him, I'll catch him.

52:59.259 --> 53:01.049
Is there anything
you can't catch?

53:01.261 --> 53:04.139
You know Bart. If anybody can
catch Bigfoot, it's him.

53:04.682 --> 53:06.850
Probably shoot him and
hang his head on the wall.

53:21.198 --> 53:23.176
Hey, it's me. You gotta
get me out of here.

53:23.200 --> 53:25.136
Why? What's the matter?

53:25.160 --> 53:27.514
We didn't hear a peep
from Bigfoot all night.

53:27.538 --> 53:29.873
And I haven't slept
and I haven't eaten,

53:30.457 --> 53:32.977
and on top of everything else, I'm
taking a crap in the woods right now.

53:33.001 --> 53:34.962
- Are you serious?
- Yes, I'm pooping right now...

53:35.546 --> 53:38.215
- while I'm talking to you.
- Ew. That is so gross.

53:38.590 --> 53:40.902
What am I supposed to do? It's not
like there are bathrooms here.

53:40.926 --> 53:44.096
First of all, you could not
call me while you're doing it.

53:44.596 --> 53:48.517
Besides, what are you
doing about toilet paper?

53:51.103 --> 53:52.383
I hadn't thought that far ahead.

53:53.731 --> 53:55.482
Oh, God. You gotta get
me out of this hell.

53:55.941 --> 53:58.026
I have some Purell, but I
don't think that's gonna...

53:59.528 --> 54:00.528
Hello?

54:00.571 --> 54:01.571
Hello?

54:01.780 --> 54:04.801
- No phones on my hunt.
- Great! That's just great!

54:04.825 --> 54:07.077
What do we do now if there's
an actual emergency?

54:07.286 --> 54:08.930
Relax. You're the expert.

54:08.954 --> 54:11.540
I will have you know, I
have low blood sugar

54:11.915 --> 54:13.685
and we haven't eaten since
we've been out here.

54:13.709 --> 54:14.918
I could get light-headed.

54:15.127 --> 54:16.879
You're hungry? Why
didn't you say so?

54:18.422 --> 54:19.590
Here.

54:28.515 --> 54:29.515
There.

54:38.734 --> 54:39.943
It's protein. It's okay.

54:47.659 --> 54:48.786
Are you mad?

54:49.161 --> 54:51.663
You better pick that up. Your
breakfast is getting away.

54:52.706 --> 54:54.291
I've lost my appetite.

54:55.125 --> 54:58.521
Have it your way. I just wouldn't
want you to die of light-headedness.

54:58.545 --> 54:59.755
You owe me an iPhone.

55:05.302 --> 55:07.179
- That'll be one dollar.
- A dollar?

55:07.971 --> 55:11.117
Unbelievable. Five bucks in the city. I'll
buy a bunch of these before we leave.

55:11.141 --> 55:12.368
When is that gonna be, actually?

55:12.392 --> 55:14.704
Well, if they don't find something
tonight, he's outta there.

55:14.728 --> 55:16.605
He's not gonna make it another night.
No way.

55:17.105 --> 55:18.875
And then this whole trip
will have been a bust.

55:18.899 --> 55:20.192
We got some footage.

55:20.818 --> 55:23.963
We can't air a show without
any Bigfoot evidence

55:23.987 --> 55:26.532
and him running around looking
scared out of his mind.

55:27.825 --> 55:28.885
Thank you.

55:28.909 --> 55:29.952
Let's go.

55:37.167 --> 55:38.502
Good evening, Jack.

55:38.919 --> 55:42.172
You've been sleeping all day,
and he's been sulking all day.

55:45.884 --> 55:49.388
Here you go, Jack. Come on over here.
All is forgiven.

55:50.180 --> 55:51.825
He knows you didn't
mean to shoot him.

55:51.849 --> 55:54.601
Why don't you tell us
all about Bigfoot?

55:54.726 --> 55:57.563
Who knows? It may help us to catch him.
Come on.

55:58.564 --> 56:02.484
- You have any of that moonshine left?
- If a snake had ears would you screw it?

56:14.413 --> 56:15.493
What are you doing tonight?

56:17.958 --> 56:18.958
Nothing.

56:22.921 --> 56:25.048
You wanna hang out,
have a couple of beers?

56:25.799 --> 56:27.342
I don't think I'm in the mood.

56:29.595 --> 56:33.223
Why don't you come over? We'll
watch a movie and make popcorn.

56:36.393 --> 56:38.687
I'm not up for a movie tonight.
Thanks, though.

56:39.313 --> 56:40.814
You sure? I make a
mean Jiffy Pop.

56:40.981 --> 56:42.441
I know you do, I just...

56:42.608 --> 56:44.610
It's been a long couple
of weeks, you know?

56:46.111 --> 56:47.111
Rain check?

56:49.281 --> 56:50.282
Any time.

56:55.370 --> 56:56.472
Night, May.

56:56.496 --> 56:57.496
Night, Park.

56:57.998 --> 56:58.998
Oh, hey...

57:02.920 --> 57:04.046
You mind?

57:04.546 --> 57:05.672
Of course not.

57:31.531 --> 57:35.285
Are you trying to tell me that
Bigfoot is really an alien?

57:35.452 --> 57:38.580
No. Not...

57:42.209 --> 57:45.253
Not just an alien...

57:47.172 --> 57:48.632
an alien criminal...

57:50.050 --> 57:54.471
who has been dropped and
left on this planet

57:55.222 --> 57:57.557
as punishment for his crimes.

57:57.683 --> 58:03.021
Are you trying to say that Earth
is like a prison for Bigfoot?

58:03.188 --> 58:04.064
Exactly.

58:04.189 --> 58:06.668
- It's a prison for Bigfoot.
- Exactly.

58:06.692 --> 58:08.443
It's a prison. The whole
thing is a prison.

58:09.987 --> 58:13.240
So when we catch him, Jack, you're
gonna have to read him his rights.

58:57.284 --> 59:00.328
Mr. Television Man, may I
ask a couple of questions?

59:00.495 --> 59:01.496
Of course, mate.

59:01.705 --> 59:03.165
Bigfoot's paws...

59:05.083 --> 59:08.628
What differentiates Bigfoot's
paws from other animals?

59:08.879 --> 59:10.714
Yeah, the...

59:11.923 --> 59:13.467
He's asking about the...

59:13.967 --> 59:15.844
- Bigfoot's paws.
- Yeah.

59:18.346 --> 59:20.992
Bigfoot scat. You ever
find any of that?

59:21.016 --> 59:22.684
That must be really interesting.

59:25.395 --> 59:26.480
- Scat?
- Scat.

59:27.189 --> 59:28.440
- Scat?
- Scat.

59:30.233 --> 59:33.445
I'm so glad you asked me
about the scat, because...

59:36.323 --> 59:39.743
Nickel for all the times school
children asked me about the scat.

59:43.580 --> 59:46.541
I guess I would say
about the scat...

59:50.128 --> 59:51.880
The scat is my favorite
part of the job.

59:52.297 --> 59:53.924
You know, put my hands in it.

59:55.300 --> 59:56.384
I get right in there.

59:57.928 --> 59:58.928
Yeah.

01:00:04.267 --> 01:00:06.603
I'm a bit drunk, but that
is definitely not a coyote.

01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:08.188
I have no idea what that was.

01:00:09.064 --> 01:00:10.784
- Maybe that's our Squatch.
- Wait a minute.

01:00:10.899 --> 01:00:12.150
Only one way to find out.

01:00:12.526 --> 01:00:13.777
What day is this?

01:00:14.736 --> 01:00:18.657
Hey, Bart. Hey, Brock.
Hey, guys?

01:00:18.865 --> 01:00:21.785
May? May, I know your secret.

01:00:23.078 --> 01:00:24.078
May?

01:00:28.083 --> 01:00:29.083
May?

01:01:09.749 --> 01:01:12.043
Get that out of my face.

01:01:12.919 --> 01:01:14.087
Come on.

01:01:19.718 --> 01:01:21.428
Guys...

01:01:22.596 --> 01:01:24.347
What the devil is
happening out here?

01:01:25.098 --> 01:01:28.101
Probably a UFO dropping
off Bigfoot prisoners.

01:01:29.144 --> 01:01:31.730
Sweet Yowie, how many monsters
you got in these woods?

01:01:31.897 --> 01:01:35.126
Hey guys, there's nothing there.
Let's go back.

01:01:35.150 --> 01:01:36.568
It's obviously something.

01:01:37.152 --> 01:01:39.297
It got our attention, you can
bet your butt it got Bigfoot's.

01:01:39.321 --> 01:01:41.340
That's why I wanna go back,
because if Bigfoot's...

01:01:41.364 --> 01:01:43.450
Jack, you're not making sense.

01:01:43.658 --> 01:01:45.076
I've gotta film
this for my show.

01:01:46.328 --> 01:01:47.370
Bart, come on...

01:01:51.833 --> 01:01:52.959
Oh, hell.

01:01:56.254 --> 01:01:57.380
What the...?

01:02:04.471 --> 01:02:09.410
Welcome to our first annual
Squatch Watch Spirit Gathering.

01:02:09.434 --> 01:02:12.371
Your what? Oh, no.
Quit that, lady.

01:02:12.395 --> 01:02:13.748
- Quit that!
- We're here to see Bigfoot.

01:02:13.772 --> 01:02:16.751
- We love Bigfoot.
- You people, you have to go.

01:02:16.775 --> 01:02:19.027
- We love Bigfoot.
- You have to get out of here.

01:02:19.236 --> 01:02:20.695
Do your loving somewhere else.

01:02:21.071 --> 01:02:23.281
Jack, come over her.
Help me out.

01:02:24.449 --> 01:02:26.677
All right, folks. My
friend here is right.

01:02:26.701 --> 01:02:31.414
This is not really the time,
definitely not the place for the...

01:02:35.001 --> 01:02:36.711
Feels kind of amazing.

01:02:40.632 --> 01:02:44.636
Jack, moonshine and tranquilizer
is not a good combination.

01:02:45.053 --> 01:02:46.388
Get the hell away from me.

01:02:47.973 --> 01:02:50.642
- He's one of us.
- One of us.

01:02:50.976 --> 01:02:52.078
One of us.

01:02:52.102 --> 01:02:54.080
I wanna be your
fuzzy little joey.

01:02:54.104 --> 01:02:56.648
One of us.

01:02:57.274 --> 01:02:58.709
What the hell is "one of us"?

01:02:58.733 --> 01:03:01.087
- We're furries.
- What the hell's a furry?

01:03:01.111 --> 01:03:03.530
A furry is a person.
They're people...

01:03:03.947 --> 01:03:07.260
who just happen to like to
dress up in furry clothes

01:03:07.284 --> 01:03:08.970
and rub up against each another.

01:03:08.994 --> 01:03:10.634
And I'll tell you
something else, Bart...

01:03:11.371 --> 01:03:14.457
I'm a furry, okay, and
I'm damn proud of it!

01:03:22.507 --> 01:03:25.260
Okay. That's it! Out of here!

01:03:25.385 --> 01:03:26.845
But, we love Bigfoot.

01:03:27.220 --> 01:03:30.181
Lady, once I have Bigfoot
stuffed and mounted,

01:03:30.307 --> 01:03:32.976
you're welcome to rub up
against him all you want.

01:03:33.143 --> 01:03:36.313
But until then, get your skinny
little chicken ass out of here.

01:03:36.521 --> 01:03:38.732
She's a bunny, Bart.
She's a bunny!

01:03:38.857 --> 01:03:40.543
- What?
- She's a bunny.

01:03:40.567 --> 01:03:42.527
It doesn't work as a chicken.
She's a bunny!

01:03:42.694 --> 01:03:44.904
Okay, then hop it
on out of here.

01:03:45.196 --> 01:03:47.532
Go on! I'm gonna count to ten.

01:03:47.657 --> 01:03:48.657
One...

01:03:48.950 --> 01:03:51.150
If you wanna come to the next
meeting, just let me know.

01:03:51.995 --> 01:03:52.995
I will.

01:03:53.830 --> 01:03:55.498
I will and I do and I will.

01:03:56.207 --> 01:03:59.794
Come on! Out!

01:04:01.171 --> 01:04:02.172
Come on!

01:04:06.885 --> 01:04:08.261
Now, as for you two.

01:04:23.068 --> 01:04:24.819
Was that a real gun
you shot back there?

01:04:25.445 --> 01:04:26.905
Yep, and I'll use it again

01:04:27.030 --> 01:04:29.282
if either one of you tries to
get into this tent tonight.

01:04:34.913 --> 01:04:36.373
Do your thing, Mr.
Television Man.

01:04:36.873 --> 01:04:37.874
What thing?

01:04:38.083 --> 01:04:40.794
You know, that howling,
yodeling thing you do.

01:04:41.378 --> 01:04:42.698
I thought you said
it was stupid.

01:04:42.879 --> 01:04:45.006
No, it's perfect.

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:46.883
You hear something?

01:04:47.050 --> 01:04:48.301
Just shut up and do it.

01:04:48.593 --> 01:04:49.761
Jack, you stay here.

01:04:53.056 --> 01:04:54.766
I need you to film me.

01:04:55.433 --> 01:04:56.433
Okay.

01:04:57.727 --> 01:04:59.080
- Okay.
- Keep that right on me.

01:04:59.104 --> 01:05:01.398
- Right.
- This is my good side.

01:05:14.244 --> 01:05:15.870
Stay on the face.
Stay on my face.

01:05:20.750 --> 01:05:23.503
He's out there. He's
definitely out there.

01:05:49.571 --> 01:05:50.613
He's getting closer.

01:06:28.860 --> 01:06:29.860
Sorry.

01:06:33.781 --> 01:06:34.781
Did I get him?

01:06:36.618 --> 01:06:37.618
Did I get him?

01:06:40.914 --> 01:06:42.081
Did I get him?

01:06:47.045 --> 01:06:48.296
Yeah, you got him.

01:06:50.882 --> 01:06:52.258
You got him, all right.

01:06:53.551 --> 01:06:58.181
Hey, Pottersville, I found Bigfoot!
Follow me!

01:06:59.891 --> 01:07:01.601
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

01:07:01.768 --> 01:07:04.354
Bigfoot can be
seen by the stars.

01:07:04.854 --> 01:07:06.105
Monster found!

01:07:08.274 --> 01:07:09.484
Pick up, pick up.

01:07:10.109 --> 01:07:12.111
Come on, May, pick up the phone.

01:07:13.613 --> 01:07:14.739
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:07:15.406 --> 01:07:18.910
what you are about to witness is
not just television history...

01:07:19.536 --> 01:07:21.996
it's also scientific history.

01:07:22.497 --> 01:07:25.291
It's also world history.

01:07:26.584 --> 01:07:32.006
It may, in fact, be the most significant
event in the history of mankind.

01:07:34.175 --> 01:07:38.471
Because I have managed to do
what no one else ever could.

01:07:39.472 --> 01:07:42.433
Which is capture the world's
most elusive beast.

01:07:44.727 --> 01:07:48.147
Without further
ado, I present...

01:07:51.818 --> 01:07:52.818
Bigfoot.

01:07:55.488 --> 01:07:56.488
Maynard!

01:07:56.990 --> 01:07:57.990
Maynard!

01:07:59.617 --> 01:08:00.660
Maynard.

01:08:02.787 --> 01:08:05.099
Maynard. What did you do to him?

01:08:05.123 --> 01:08:07.208
I caught him. That's
my job, isn't it?

01:08:07.375 --> 01:08:09.085
- This isn't Bigfoot!
- Of course it is.

01:08:09.294 --> 01:08:12.439
Is this really what you do for a living?
This is Maynard Greiger.

01:08:12.463 --> 01:08:14.507
He runs the general store.

01:08:14.924 --> 01:08:16.009
Maynard.

01:08:18.386 --> 01:08:19.970
- Maynard.
- Shit.

01:08:20.513 --> 01:08:22.866
It's okay, Park. He's
gonna be all right.

01:08:22.890 --> 01:08:25.077
I just popped him with
a tranquilizer dart.

01:08:25.100 --> 01:08:28.520
Was that you in the
forest this entire time?

01:08:29.354 --> 01:08:31.482
Maynard, are you okay?

01:08:32.942 --> 01:08:34.234
So, this is all a big hoax?

01:08:36.112 --> 01:08:37.572
Cameras off!

01:08:37.779 --> 01:08:40.073
- Hey...
- This is a big hoax, isn't it?

01:08:41.783 --> 01:08:43.202
Do you know who I am?

01:08:44.203 --> 01:08:45.872
This was gonna be my
biggest show ever!

01:08:46.413 --> 01:08:47.915
It was gonna make me a star!

01:08:49.709 --> 01:08:50.877
Well, guess what?

01:08:51.419 --> 01:08:53.296
I am gonna sue Pottersville.

01:08:54.671 --> 01:08:55.671
How do you like that?

01:08:57.008 --> 01:08:58.718
That's right. You'll be ruined!

01:09:00.053 --> 01:09:04.241
I don't care if a colony of Bigfoot
moves in and builds houses,

01:09:04.265 --> 01:09:06.493
and starts raising their kids and
marching their kids back and forth

01:09:06.517 --> 01:09:09.580
to school across the square every day,
and singing karaoke at the karaoke bar!

01:09:09.604 --> 01:09:11.022
No one's ever gonna see it!

01:09:11.397 --> 01:09:12.499
Because from now on,

01:09:12.523 --> 01:09:17.694
Pottersville will be known as a
town of fakes and phonies...

01:09:20.113 --> 01:09:21.240
and freaks.

01:09:24.118 --> 01:09:25.370
G'day, morons.

01:09:28.706 --> 01:09:31.084
Did somebody say they
needed a Bigfoot?

01:09:31.751 --> 01:09:34.837
Well, nice work, Maynard, now the
whole town is gonna get sued.

01:09:35.921 --> 01:09:37.173
There goes Christmas.

01:09:37.590 --> 01:09:39.634
And we can all kiss a
Happy New Year goodbye.

01:09:42.011 --> 01:09:44.346
I ought to stick a "big
foot" up your ass.

01:09:49.310 --> 01:09:50.812
Hey, little bunny.

01:09:51.729 --> 01:09:55.149
I was thinking maybe I can
come over later and...

01:09:55.942 --> 01:09:59.821
I'd love for you to come by tomorrow,
Maynard, and pack your stuff and leave.

01:10:00.446 --> 01:10:02.407
We all just wanted
to meet Bigfoot,

01:10:02.865 --> 01:10:05.034
and you made us look
like a bunch of idiots.

01:10:08.496 --> 01:10:09.706
I'm sorry.

01:10:18.631 --> 01:10:19.924
You okay, pal?

01:10:31.936 --> 01:10:33.646
So you will be seeking
legal action?

01:10:33.771 --> 01:10:34.957
That's right, yeah.

01:10:34.981 --> 01:10:38.127
It's the opposite of a class-action suit,
because it's me against 80 people.

01:10:38.151 --> 01:10:40.778
It's like un-classy suit.

01:10:41.404 --> 01:10:44.991
It's not what you call it, but
I'm suing for damages, yeah.

01:10:45.408 --> 01:10:47.177
I have heard a
number, an estimate,

01:10:47.201 --> 01:10:50.621
somewhere in the ballpark of 150
million dollars in damages.

01:10:50.747 --> 01:10:52.498
Is that what you
will be seeking?

01:10:52.832 --> 01:10:55.626
I couldn't say, and I won't say.

01:10:55.835 --> 01:10:58.588
I'm not allowed to say,
but that's accurate, yes.

01:11:00.631 --> 01:11:04.635
I can't promise you anybody's gonna show
up, I mean, people are pretty upset.

01:11:04.844 --> 01:11:06.644
But you know his heart
was in the right place.

01:11:07.013 --> 01:11:10.016
Yeah. Well, I'll do my best.

01:11:53.851 --> 01:11:57.104
Hi. Is there a Maynard
Greiger here?

01:11:57.855 --> 01:11:59.190
I don't get it.

01:11:59.649 --> 01:12:04.111
Don't you know how much he loves
you, how much he loves this town?

01:12:06.823 --> 01:12:11.869
Maynard's family has owned and operated
the general store for generations.

01:12:12.078 --> 01:12:15.331
He's over there right now,
packing up his shop because...

01:12:16.374 --> 01:12:18.334
he doesn't know what else to do.

01:12:19.043 --> 01:12:20.711
He feels like he
doesn't belong here.

01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:23.756
Well, he did ruin our shot.

01:12:24.298 --> 01:12:25.716
Your shot at what?

01:12:26.342 --> 01:12:30.096
Fame, fortune. Being on TV.

01:12:30.263 --> 01:12:32.139
And how did he ruin it, exactly?

01:12:32.431 --> 01:12:34.350
By pretending to be Bigfoot.

01:12:34.725 --> 01:12:37.645
How much Bigfoot merchandise
did you sell out of his store?

01:12:40.648 --> 01:12:42.400
Did you ever offer him anything?

01:12:43.276 --> 01:12:45.778
Did he ever ask for
anything in return?

01:12:46.904 --> 01:12:49.031
He's given everything
to Pottersville.

01:12:49.448 --> 01:12:51.158
I mean everything.

01:12:52.869 --> 01:12:56.622
He's tried so hard to keep us and
this town afloat that, honestly,

01:12:56.873 --> 01:12:59.017
I don't know if he could
afford to keep his store open

01:12:59.041 --> 01:13:00.793
even if he felt like
you wanted him to.

01:13:08.301 --> 01:13:10.553
You've all seen this.
You know what it's for.

01:13:11.304 --> 01:13:14.265
And at one time or another, when
you were down on your luck,

01:13:14.599 --> 01:13:18.227
each and every one of you asked Maynard
to put your name in this book.

01:13:19.270 --> 01:13:20.938
Has he ever refused any of you?

01:13:22.732 --> 01:13:26.485
Now when he needs our help, your
answer is to turn your back on him?

01:13:27.570 --> 01:13:29.947
Well, before you decide
that he ruined your shot,

01:13:30.489 --> 01:13:34.452
or your Christmas, or your Happy New Year,
I just want you to take a look at this.

01:13:36.162 --> 01:13:39.040
Then you can tell me if you're still
upset with him for pretending.

01:13:48.633 --> 01:13:49.759
It's empty.

01:13:52.678 --> 01:13:53.721
Yeah.

01:14:09.528 --> 01:14:11.864
Now we go live
to Stacy Gutierrez

01:14:12.031 --> 01:14:16.160
for a story you'll only find
here on Channel 13 News. Stacy.

01:14:16.577 --> 01:14:17.745
Thank you, John.

01:14:17.954 --> 01:14:23.018
Hi, this is Stacy Gutierrez
reporting live on Christmas Eve

01:14:23.042 --> 01:14:26.605
here in Pottersville, but
all is not merry and bright

01:14:26.629 --> 01:14:30.049
as the town is still reeling
from the Bigfoot hoax.

01:14:30.466 --> 01:14:34.971
Well, I am here with the hoaxster
himself, Maynard Greiger,

01:14:35.096 --> 01:14:36.639
to get his side of the story.

01:14:36.806 --> 01:14:39.016
So, Mr. Greiger,
why did you do it?

01:14:40.810 --> 01:14:44.105
Well, I never meant for
it to happen, really.

01:14:46.023 --> 01:14:49.402
But when people started
really thinking I was Bigfoot

01:14:49.819 --> 01:14:53.239
and I saw how happy it made
them, I figured, why not?

01:14:53.698 --> 01:14:56.367
Why do you think this town
was so captivated by him?

01:14:56.909 --> 01:15:00.663
I don't think it's just our town, really.
I mean, it could be any town.

01:15:01.956 --> 01:15:04.583
People everywhere are looking
for something to believe in.

01:15:05.918 --> 01:15:09.755
We had fallen on hard times,
like a lot of other places...

01:15:11.173 --> 01:15:14.468
this magical sense of...
well, Bigfoot,

01:15:14.593 --> 01:15:17.263
you know, that sense that
something else was out there.

01:15:18.180 --> 01:15:20.016
It really brought
the town together.

01:15:20.266 --> 01:15:23.686
I haven't seen this town so
alive in a long time, and...

01:15:26.063 --> 01:15:30.609
It seemed to give everybody the faith and
hope that things were gonna be okay.

01:15:31.777 --> 01:15:33.404
I guess that's why I did it.

01:15:35.072 --> 01:15:38.784
If you had to do it all
over again, would you?

01:15:43.372 --> 01:15:48.270
You know, let's just say that hope
isn't always the most realistic thing,

01:15:48.294 --> 01:15:51.839
but it tends to make the
world a better place.

01:15:54.216 --> 01:15:55.634
Thank you, Mr. Greiger.

01:15:56.302 --> 01:15:58.637
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas to you.

01:15:59.263 --> 01:16:03.059
This is Stacy Gutierrez
live from Pottersville.

01:16:05.519 --> 01:16:07.354
Thank you, Mr. Greiger,
that was great.

01:16:07.772 --> 01:16:09.148
My pleasure. You're welcome.

01:16:12.735 --> 01:16:14.236
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:16:14.403 --> 01:16:16.238
I have some friends who
want to talk to you.

01:16:17.865 --> 01:16:19.450
Hey, fellas. What's going on?

01:16:20.034 --> 01:16:22.578
Thanks for letting us sell
our stuff out of your store.

01:16:23.162 --> 01:16:26.415
And thank you also for just...
well...

01:16:28.709 --> 01:16:29.794
Oh, what the hell.

01:16:36.926 --> 01:16:38.219
You're welcome.

01:16:40.679 --> 01:16:41.615
Hey, Tammy.

01:16:41.639 --> 01:16:44.433
I'm sorry I was so
hard on you, Maynard.

01:16:51.607 --> 01:16:53.794
Hey. Yeah, we've gotta
get back on the air.

01:16:53.818 --> 01:16:56.112
There's another breaking
story happening here now.

01:16:56.821 --> 01:16:58.131
You could never
ruin our Christmas.

01:16:58.155 --> 01:16:59.156
Thanks, Doris.

01:17:00.074 --> 01:17:02.636
Maynard, forget the things I said.
Merry Christmas.

01:17:02.660 --> 01:17:03.744
Thank you.

01:17:04.286 --> 01:17:05.286
Thanks.

01:17:07.873 --> 01:17:12.128
Maynard, I'm so sorry I said
I'd put my foot up your ass.

01:17:13.379 --> 01:17:14.397
It's okay, Millie.

01:17:14.421 --> 01:17:16.841
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas, Millie.

01:17:20.594 --> 01:17:21.804
- Hey, Maynard.
- Jasper.

01:17:21.929 --> 01:17:23.347
Thanks for everything, man.

01:17:25.099 --> 01:17:27.268
Yeah. Sure.

01:17:27.393 --> 01:17:29.270
- Hey.
- Yeah?

01:17:29.812 --> 01:17:32.439
You thought you had to become
Bigfoot to save this town,

01:17:32.565 --> 01:17:35.985
but you saved it a long
time ago by just being you.

01:17:37.069 --> 01:17:41.699
Hi, this is Stacy Gutierrez
reporting live on Christmas Eve

01:17:41.907 --> 01:17:44.618
from Greiger's General Store
here in Pottersville,

01:17:44.910 --> 01:17:49.248
where the entire community has
turned out in a show of support

01:17:49.415 --> 01:17:53.169
for the one-time Bigfoot
hoaxster Maynard Greiger,

01:17:53.502 --> 01:17:56.839
to receive him now as
their hometown hero.

01:17:58.048 --> 01:17:59.048
Hey, buddy.

01:18:00.759 --> 01:18:03.304
It's truly a Christmas miracle.

01:18:05.389 --> 01:18:06.891
Hi. Thanks, Maynard.

01:18:07.266 --> 01:18:09.393
- Merry Christmas, Maynard.
- Merry Christmas.

01:18:14.899 --> 01:18:16.525
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:18:17.985 --> 01:18:19.486
What are you doing later?

01:18:24.533 --> 01:18:26.827
I think you should close
up and come home.

01:18:29.371 --> 01:18:31.874
You can bring the
Bigfoot costume.

01:18:35.711 --> 01:18:37.631
I've been wanting to talk
to you for a long time.

01:18:37.713 --> 01:18:40.090
I know you have.

01:18:41.300 --> 01:18:42.426
You were right.

01:18:44.011 --> 01:18:45.346
I know, baby.

01:18:46.055 --> 01:18:47.657
Your little bunny's
always right.

01:18:47.681 --> 01:18:48.974
No, you were right...

01:18:54.146 --> 01:18:55.356
We should split up.

01:18:57.066 --> 01:18:58.126
Excuse me?

01:18:58.150 --> 01:18:59.443
You should be happy.

01:18:59.902 --> 01:19:03.572
You should go and find whatever
excitement you can in life,

01:19:03.739 --> 01:19:04.865
if that's what you want.

01:19:05.616 --> 01:19:06.616
I get it.

01:19:07.284 --> 01:19:08.494
Life is short.

01:19:09.328 --> 01:19:10.579
Why not be happy?

01:19:12.373 --> 01:19:14.333
That's all I wanted to tell you.

01:19:15.292 --> 01:19:16.502
I don't...

01:19:19.838 --> 01:19:21.006
Wait. Are you...?

01:19:25.678 --> 01:19:26.804
This is it?

01:19:44.822 --> 01:19:49.618
Hey, Parker, is that rain check
still available for the Jiffy Pop?

01:19:53.747 --> 01:19:54.873
Always.

01:20:01.755 --> 01:20:02.798
To Maynard Greiger...

01:20:04.008 --> 01:20:05.527
the richest man in Pottersville.

01:20:05.551 --> 01:20:07.428
Hear, hear.

01:20:10.055 --> 01:20:11.908
Hey. Norm? Tony?

01:20:11.932 --> 01:20:14.935
You say people all over the
world love this Bigfoot, right?

01:20:15.102 --> 01:20:16.913
Um, yeah.

01:20:16.937 --> 01:20:20.524
On every continent and
in every language.

01:20:20.691 --> 01:20:21.942
- All of them.
- Yeah.

01:20:23.193 --> 01:20:24.193
All right.

01:20:30.909 --> 01:20:33.138
Ladies and gentlemen,
I've just received word

01:20:33.162 --> 01:20:36.099
it appears that Brock Masterson,
host of Monster Finder,

01:20:36.123 --> 01:20:38.101
is also not who he claims to be.

01:20:38.125 --> 01:20:41.104
In an exclusive story you'll only
see here on Channel 13 News,

01:20:41.128 --> 01:20:45.424
we've discovered that Brock Masterson
is actually one Leonard Abromowitz,

01:20:45.841 --> 01:20:47.843
an actor from Coney Island.

01:20:48.218 --> 01:20:50.864
Last time I checked, that's
nowhere near Australia.

01:20:50.888 --> 01:20:52.139
Well, what do you know?

01:21:24.630 --> 01:21:26.441
Hey, you two. What
are you doing?

01:21:26.465 --> 01:21:28.485
We're just here to meet
Bill on his lunch break.

01:21:28.509 --> 01:21:30.528
This place is amazing, you two.

01:21:30.552 --> 01:21:31.696
Thanks, Maynard!

01:21:31.720 --> 01:21:33.138
- You bet ya.
- Have fun.

